Sponsorships

The Sponsorship section provides an overview of our Global Sponsorship Strategy along with a summary of our Sponsorship properties. Additionally, this section offers a behind the scenes look at sponsorship and marketing teams on the ground and our Team Visa athletes.

  • Strategy
  • Top 5
  • Team Visa
  • Properties

FIFA Confederations Cup (FCC) Brazil 2013

Jogo Bonito – Beautiful Game

  1. The official emblem of the FIFA Confederations Cup Brazil 2013 (FCC) features a stylized interpretation of Brazil's national bird, the Rufous-Bellied Thrush (Sabía-Laranjeira).
  2. High levels of Visa activation onsite including 500-1500 POS terminals, 34 ATM's, and 11 Customer Service Kiosks.
  3. Innovation and technology will take the pitch for the first time ever at an FCC when FIFA implements Goal Line Technology (GLT).
  4. Total prize money at the FCC will be up 14% compared with the last edition. In total a prize pool of $20m USD will be shared among the eight participating nations.
  5. 200+ Visa staff will be onsite to help activate and support Visa's second ever FIFA Confederations Cup.
